  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Creating Spaces for Peace - Phase four: Supporting local peacebuilding and local citizen-state relations</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building on the achievements of the previous three phases thus far, and as well as context analyses, scenario-planning meetings and discussion sessions that the Alert Lebanon Team has been conducting to capture implications of the above-mentioned contextual developments on peacebuilding work in Lebanon, the fourth phase will mainly focus on supporting citizen relations (horizontal linkages) and peacebuilding prospects, and on improving citizen-state relations (vertical linkages) at the local level. The fourth phase will also consolidate and disseminate learning on local peacebuilding and conflict sensitivity and capitalize on this process for influencing and local advocacy. This phase sees a stronger focus on real time context monitoring and analysis to share with partners given the evolving dynamics and seeks to leverage the HSD&#x2019;s expertise, networks and partnerships to enhance peacebuilding impact and contribute to the Communities of Practice related to peacebuilding in Lebanon. 

The approach for phase 4 involves: 1) regular stakeholder engagement, context analysis and monitoring; 2) convening and expanding spaces for dialogue, both horizontal (inter- and intra-community) and vertical (citizen-local government relations) through action; 3) capacity development and accompaniment of municipalities and grassroots groups for inclusive, multi-stakeholder networking, engagement and dialogue, collaborative/joint action and conflict sensitivity; 4) technical advice and support, advocacy, exchange and learning on peacebuilding and conflict sensitivity; 5) capitalisation and sustainability planning.

The proposed set of activities in this phase is for a project lasting 15 months from October 2020 to December 2021.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">No implementing partners.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SO 1: To strengthen and sustain local/grassroot capacity for conflict mediation and networking developed through the &#x2018;Creating Space for Peace&#x2019; dialogue mechanism and local advocacy process. 
SO 2: To strengthen and sustain local authorities&#x2019; (municipalities) capacity for conflict sensitive service provision and improve citizen-local authority relations through community engagement.
SO 3: To enhance learning and influencing for peacebuilding and conflict sensitivity through tailored support, collecting and testing evidence for approaches and disseminating lessons learned.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Youth groups in Bekaa and Tripoli and two municipalities in Bekaa.</narrative>
  </description>
